casebody.data:
The Central National Bank of the City of New York, Respondent, v. Leonard D. White, et al., Appellants. Decided May 3, 1886. Appeal from order permitting plaintiff, upon terms, to comply with a certain previous order as to which it was in default. Edwards & Odell, for appellants. Martin & Smith, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J. and Freedman, J.

Opinion

Per Curiam.

Order affirmed, with costs.
